name: Squat
description:
Squat is a type of bodyweight exercise. It is one of the most popular exercises for strength and muscle growth. Squat is particularly effective for focusing on the muscles of the leg and hips.
Squat are an easy exercise for beginners to do. It can help strengthen leg muscles, tighten hip muscles and burn calories to lose weight.
It tightens the butt and legs. Squats are very effective for firming and strengthening your legs by acting on the gluteus,hip flexors, quadriceps, hamstrings and inner thigh muscles. Also, bodyweight squats can help shape your glutes and butt.

name: Squat Thrust
description: The burpee, or squat thrust, is a full body exercise used in strength training and as an aerobic exercise. The basic movement is performed in four steps and known as a four-count burpee: Begin in a standing position. Move into a squat position with your hands on the ground. (count 1) Kick your feet back into a plank position, while keeping your arms extended. (count 2) Immediately return your feet into squat position. (count 3) Stand up from the squat position (count 4)

ollibSet up the box: /bPosition the box behind you, about 3 feet from a squat rack if you're using a barbell. Choose a height that allows you to squat down and gently tap your glutes on the box with your back straight./lilibStand with proper form: /bStand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointed slightly outward. Engage your core and keep your back neutral. If using a barbell, rack it at shoulder height./lilibLower down: /bSit back as if going to sit on a chair, bending your knees and lowering your hips towards the box. Keep your core tight and back straight throughout the movement./lilibControlled descent: /bDescend in a controlled manner until your glutes gently touch the box. Don't plop down./lilibPause and press up: /bBriefly pause at the bottom with your back straight and core engaged. Then, press through your heels to drive yourself back up to the starting position./li/ol
Improvements in coordination, balance and endurance, toning of the leg and buttock muscles and an overall increase in bone density eliminating the risk of osteoporosis.

name: Squat box
description: Ol li b Prepare the box: /b position the box behind you, about a meter and a half from a rack for the squat if you use a barbell.Choose a height that allows you to crouch and gently beat the buttocks on the box with a straight back.to the width of the shoulders and the tips of the feet slightly facing outwards.Commit the core and keep your back neutral.If you use a barbell, place it at the shoulders. /li li b lower: /b sit as if you have to sit on a chair, bending your knees and lowering your hips towards the box.Keep the tense core and the back straight throughout the movement.Do not throw yourself to the ground. /li li b pause and rise: /b make a short break on the bottom with a straight back and busy core.Then, press on the heels to trace the starting position. /li /ol improves coordination, balance and resistance, tones the muscles of the legs and buttocks and increases bone density by eliminating the risk of osteoporosis.

name: Squat con barra
description:
Controla la bajada, baja en 2 segundos y sube lo más explosivo que puedas.
Es muy importante que hagas movilidad de cadera antes de empezar a entrenar, para mejorar la profundidad.
Olvidate del peso, baja todo lo que puedas, sin levantar los talones del suelo y sube par arriba.
Una buena técnica va a generarte más hipertrofia que mucho peso sin un ROM correcto.

name: Squat con bilanciere

È molto importante eseguire la mobilità dell'anca prima di iniziare l'allenamento, per migliorare la profondità. Dimentica il peso, scendi più che puoi, senza sollevare i talloni da terra e sali. Una buona tecnica genererà più ipertrofia di molto peso senza un corretto ROM.

description: Place a barbell in a rack just below shoulder-height. Dip under the bar to put it behind the neck across the top of the back, and grip the bar with the hands wider than shoulder-width apart. Lift the chest up and squeeze the shoulder blades together to keep the straight back throughout the entire movement. Stand up to bring the bar off the rack and step backwards, then place the feet so that they are a little wider than shoulder-width apart. Sit back into hips and keep the back straight and the chest up, squatting down so the hips are below the knees. From the bottom of the squat, press feet into the ground and push hips forward to return to the top of the standing position.

description: Get onto the calf raises machine, you should able to completely push your calves down. Stand straight, don't make a hollow back and don't bend your legs. Pull yourself up as high as you can. Make a small pause of 1 - 2 seconds and go slowly down.

name: Standing Calf Stretch
description: This stretch targets the gastrocnemius (the chief muscle of the calf of the leg, which flexes the knee and foot). It is easy to perform anywhere. All you need is a wall or a chair.

name: Standing Rope Forearm
description: Grab a wrist roller tool with both hands while standing with your feet about shoulder width apart. If your gym does not have a wrist roller tool, you can easily put one together. All you need is a 5 or 10 pound weight plate, a strong thin rope about 3 feet long and a 6-8 inch stick or bar. Securely fasten the rope to the middle of the bar/stick and tie the other end of the rope to the weight plate. To begin this exercise, grab the bar/stick with both hands using an overhand grip. Extend both arms straight out in front of you, parallel to the floor. Next, roll the weight up from the floor by rapidly twisting the bar/stick with your hands and wrists. Once the weight reaches the top, slowly lower the plate back to the floor by reversing the motion of your hands and wrists. Repeat (if you can!).

name: Standing Soleus Stretch

name: Sumo Deadlift
description:
ol
liBegin with a bar loaded on the ground. Approach the bar so that the bar intersects the middle of the feet. The feet should be set very wide, near the collars. Bend at the hips to grip the bar. The arms should be directly below the shoulders, inside the legs, and you can use a pronated grip, a mixed grip, or hook grip. Relax the shoulders, which in effect lengthens your arms./li
liTake a breath, and then lower your hips, looking forward with your head with your chest up. Drive through the floor, spreading your feet apart, with your weight on the back half of your feet. Extend through the hips and knees./li
liAs the bar passes through the knees, lean back and drive the hips into the bar, pulling your shoulder blades together./li
liReturn the weight to the ground by bending at the hips and controlling the weight on the way down./li
/ol

name: Sumo Squats
description:
Stand with your feet wider than your shoulders, with your toes pointed out at a 45 degree angle and barbell on your shoulder.
While keeping your back straight, descend slowly by bending at the knees and hips as if you are sitting down (squatting).
Lower yourself until your quadriceps and hamstrings are parallel to the floor.
Return to the starting position by pressing upwards and extending your legs while maintaining an equal distribution of weight on your forefoot and heel.

name: Superman
description: Legen Sie sich flach auf den Bauch und strecken Sie die Arme vor sich auf den Boden, während Ihre Beine flach liegen. Heben Sie beide Arme und Beine gleichzeitig an, als ob Sie fliegen würden, und ziehen Sie den unteren Rücken zusammen. Stellen Sie sicher, dass Sie atmen und halten Sie die Bewegung, abhängig von Ihrer Fitness, mindestens zwei bis fünf Sekunden pro Wiederholung.

name: Superman
description: Lay flat on your stomach with your arms extended in front of you on the ground as your legs are lying flat. Lift both your arms and legs at the same time, as if you were flying, and contract the lower back. Make sure that you are breathing and, depending on your fitness level, hold the movement for at least two to five seconds per repetition.

name: T-Bar Rudern (breit)
description:
Die Ausführung ist sehr ähnlich wie beim freien vorgebeugtem Rudern, nur ist hier die Stange fest.
Stelle dich auf das Gerät in die entsprechende Stelle und greife die Gewichtsstange mit mittelbreitem Griff. Gehe etwas in die Knie, bringe die Brust raus und führe den Oberkörper nach vorne. Hebe das Gewicht und ziehe es in Richtung Bauchnabel hoch (Ellenbogen am Körper lassen). Lasse es dann langsam wieder runter und spüre die Dehnung in den Kreuzmuskeln.

name: T-Bar row

name: TRX - Biceps curl to one arm
description:
colocar las cintas cruzadas, para dejar toda la fuerza en una sola cuerda y que sea más seguro el ejercicio.

Para su realización nos vamos a colocar inclinados lateralmente. El brazo con el que vamos a trabajar será el que agarre la cinta del TRX que hemos montado combinando los dos agarres. El otro brazo lo dejaremos relajado lateralmente, ya que no actuará en este momento, pues sólo entrará en acción la parte del bíceps del brazo que tenemos agarrado a la cinta. El cuerpo, al igual que anteriormente, permanecerá recto, mirando al frente y cuanto más nos inclinemos mayor será la resistencia que tengamos que vencer durante el ejercicio. Ambas piernas, en este caso, estarán juntas para solamente mantener el brazo estirado para doblarlo por el codo. Este movimiento activará el bíceps y con ello trabajaremos esta parte del brazo.

name: TRX Rudern
description: Rudern mit Schlingentrainer - Körpergewichtsübung

name: TRX Tricep Extension
description:
Attach the TRX or other suspension system overhead, having the handles hanging at chest level or slightly lower. Experiment to see what height allows you to set up in the best way.
Stand in front of the handles and grab them with your palms facing down.
Engage your abs, squeeze your glutes, take a breath and lean forward, lifting your heels off the floor. Keep your elbows straight.
Take another breath and lower yourself slowly by bending your elbows. 
Go down until your elbows are at a 90-degree angle (to the point where your wrists are above your elbows). Hold the position for a moment.
Extend your arms by engaging your triceps and bring yourself to the starting position as you exhale.

name: TRX dips
description:
Start with the hands on the suspension trainer and feet on the ground.
Your hands should be under your shoulders with the feet slightly in front.
Lower yourself by bringing the hips between the handles and flexing the elbows.
Extend the elbows to come back to the starting position and repeat.

name: TRX gorilla biceps curl
description: Nos colocaremos de frente a las cintas del TRX y las agarraremos con los puños de las manos enfrentados y al frente, con los brazos totalmente estirados a la altura más o menos de los hombros. El cuerpo lo mantendremos recto hacia atrás, como en los anteriores ejercicios, ya que lo que vamos a hacer es mediante la activación de los bíceps, elevar el cuerpo hacia las cintas del TRX.El cuerpo estará recto y los pies apoyados en el suelo. Los brazos en esta ocasión, los vamos a colocar abiertos hacia los lados, y a la altura del pecho. El movimiento que vamos a hacer será una contracción hacia el pecho. Para conseguirlo, lo que haremos será doblar los codos para que, mediante la activación de los bíceps atraigamos el cuerpo hacia las cintas.

name: TRX hammer curl - biceps
description: Colocar los agarres como si de una continuación de las cintas se tratase. Colocaremos los brazos estirados hacia adelante y el cuerpo hacia atrás totalmente recto. Los músculos de los bíceps se activarán al doblar los codos para atraer el cuerpo hacia las cintas. El movimiento de contracción terminará con un ligero movimiento de las manos hacia afuera, debido al agarre que estamos teniendo.

name: TRX roll out
description:
sostener las empuñaduras con las manos, alargar los brazos y mantenerlos paralelos a la altura del pecho. El movimiento que debes realizar es una abertura de los brazos alineados con los hombros mientas inclinas el cuerpo hacia delante. Intenta no realizar una extensión de hombro más allá de los 90º y mantén contraída la musculatura abdominal y los glúteos.
Músculos implicados: Transverso, recto abdominal y erectores espinales

name: TRX- biceps gorila
description:
Nos colocaremos de frente a las cintas del TRX y las agarraremos con los puños de las manos enfrentados y al frente, con los brazos totalmente estirados a la altura más o menos de los hombros. El cuerpo lo mantendremos recto hacia atrás, como en los anteriores ejercicios, ya que lo que vamos a hacer es mediante la activación de los bíceps, elevar el cuerpo hacia las cintas del TRX.
El cuerpo estará recto y los pies apoyados en el suelo. Los brazos en esta ocasión, los vamos a colocar abiertos hacia los lados, y a la altura del pecho. El movimiento que vamos a hacer será una contracción hacia el pecho. Para conseguirlo, lo que haremos será doblar los codos para que, mediante la activación de los bíceps atraigamos el cuerpo hacia las cintas.

name: Trazioni alla sbarra
description: Il chin-up (noto anche come mento o chinup) è un esercizio di allenamento della forza. Le persone spesso eseguono questo esercizio con l'intenzione di rafforzare muscoli come il gran dorsale e il bicipite, che rispettivamente estendono la spalla e flettono il gomito. In questa manovra, i palmi sono rivolti verso il corpo. È una forma di pull-up in cui il range di movimento è stabilito in relazione al mento di una persona.

name: Trazioni alla sbarra commando

name: Tricep Dumbbell Kickback
description:
ol
liStart with a dumbbell in each hand and your palms facing your torso. Keep your back straight with a slight bend in the knees and bend forward at the waist. Your torso should be almost parallel to the floor. Make sure to keep your head up. Your upper arms should be close to your torso and parallel to the floor. Your forearms should be pointed towards the floor as you hold the weights. There should be a 90-degree angle formed between your forearm and upper arm. This is your starting position./li
liNow, while keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and use your triceps to lift the weights until the arm is fully extended. Focus on moving the forearm./li
liAfter a brief pause at the top contraction, inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position./li
liRepeat the movement for the prescribed amount of repetitions./li
/ol
strongVariations:/strong This exercise can be executed also one arm at a time much like the one arm rows are performed.
Also, if you like the one arm variety, you can use a low pulley handle instead of a dumbbell for better peak contraction. In this case, the palms should be facing up (supinated grip) as opposed to the torso (neutral grip).

name: Tricep Pushdown on Cable
description: The cable rope push-down is a popular exercise targeting the triceps muscles. It's easy to learn and perform, making it a favorite for everyone from beginners to advanced lifters. It is usually performed for moderate to high reps, such as 8-12 reps or more per set, as part of an upper-body or arm-focused workout.

name: Triceps Extensions on Cable
description: Grab the cable, stand with your feet shoulder wide, keep your back straight and lean forward a little. Push the bar down, making sure the elbows don't move during the exercise. Rotate your hands outwards at the very end and go back to the initial position without pause.

name: Triceps Extensions on Cable With Bar
description: Grab the bar, stand with your feet shoulder wide, keep your back straight and lean forward a little. Push the bar down, making sure the elbows don't move during the exercise. Without pause go back to the initial position.

name: Triceps Pushdown
description: Triceps pushdown on cable using lat bar.

name: Triceps stretch left
description: Put your right hand on your back, use your left hand to grab your right elbow and gently pull it. Hold this position for a few seconds.

name: Triceps stretch right
description: Put your right hand on your back, use your left hand to grab your right elbow and gently pull it. Hold this position for a few seconds.

name: Trizeps Seildrücken
description: Stelle dich mit schulterbreitem Stand vor dem Kabelzug, beuge den Rücken sehr leicht nach vorn und greife das Seil. Ziehe nun nach unten, wobei die Ellenbogen sich während der ganzen Übung nicht von der Stelle bewegen sollen. Wenn die Arme ausgestreckt sind, drehe die Hände nach außen. olliWith arms in the Y position, lift your chest slightly from the ground, creating a pull tension in your arms upward./liliHold this position for several seconds (15–30 is ideal)./liliKeeping your chest up, bend at your elbows to move from a Y position to a "W" position, with arms bent at the elbows and maintaining the upward tension./liliHold for around as long as with the Y position./liliStill with your chest up, move to a "T" position, straightening your arms out to the side to be perpendicular to your body./liliHold for around as long as you held the W position./liliMove from the T position to the W position, then from the W position to the Y position./liliRepeat./li/ol

name: Yoga exercise: Cow-cat
description: First get into the four-footed stance. The hands are underneath the shoulders. The fingers are fanned out wide and ensure a stable stance. It is best to rest your front body weight on your thumbs and index fingers. Now place your legs hip-width apart on the yoga mat. Your thighs should be vertically below your hips. Make sure that your weight is evenly distributed between your hands and knees. Your head is an extension of your spine and you are looking down at your mat. Your back is in a neutral position. Breathe in deeply and start with the cat. With the next exhalation, round your back vertebra by vertebra. Try to pull yourself as far as possible towards the ceiling. Pull your head towards your chest and tilt your pelvis. Now inhale deeply and move into the opposite position, cow pose. Bend your back down, pull your shoulders back slightly and lift your head as far as is comfortable for you. Your gaze is directed upwards. Breathe out consciously and switch back to the cat. With the next exhalation, switch back to cow. Repeat the exercise a few times and make sure that you are in the flow.

name: Squats
description:
The squat exercise plays a key role for the development of the lower part of the body, while its effectiveness and safety depend on the technique of execution.This includes the correct setting of the legs, the depth of squat, the position of the knees and socks, as well as the place of laying the bar.Beginners are recommended to follow classical technology, not lift, if they do not engage in powerlifting.

Standing: become straight by placing your feet shoulder -width apart, socks are slightly expanded to the sides.

Capture of the bar: go to the bar, placing it on the top of the back (not too low).Grab the bar with both hands.

Initial position: take your legs back and stand in a full vertical position, holding the bar on your shoulders.

Fulfillment: Start sinking, pushing the pelvis back, as if sitting on a chair until the hips are parallel to the floor or slightly lower.Make sure your knees are directed in the same direction as the socks and do not go beyond the line.

Return to the starting position: by pressing the heels, rise back to the vertical position.

Repeat: Perform the recommended number of repetitions.

Note: If you experience difficulties in holding the heels on the floor during a squat, use small heels.With the right technique and the performance of squats, especially deep, the buttocks are actively included in the work.

Step:  ol li Standard push -ups: 1.A bending the arm until the chest is almost exposed to the ground to ensure that the back is straight.1.B to raise yourself to the starting position with your arm.2. Turn your body to one side to make your back straight, support the bottom of the body to completely stretch, and touch the ground with only the bottom and the feet at the bottom./li li Repeat, each time in step 2./li /ol

name: Sit-ups
description: Starting posture: Standing in the face of chairs.  Step:  ol li Walk to the chair./li li Go down from the chair./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Sit-ups
description: Starting posture: Bend your knees and lie down on the floor.  Step:  OL li Bend your shoulders towards the pelvis.Put your hands behind your neck or next to the neck, or you can cross your chest.2. Back to the initial posture./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Voldemort
description: Starting posture: Sit on the ground, support the ground back to support the upper body.Fingers to point forward.Bend your knees and close your feet.  Step:  ol li Lift your hips, leave the ground, straighten your arms./li li Bend the elbow, the hips are down./li li Straighten your arm and return to the previous position./li li Repeat step 2 and step 3./li /ol  Note: The difficulty of practice depends on how high the hips are supported.

name: push-up
description: Starting posture: First, do the starting posture of push -ups, touch the ground with your hands with your hands, and straighten your back, arms and legs.To do this posture, you can lie on the ground, put your hands down beside your head, and lift your arms until your arms are straight.  Step:  ol li Bend the elbow until your chest is almost exposed to the ground.Make sure your back is always straight./li li Use your arms to support yourself and return to the starting position./li li Repeat the above action./li /ol

name: Putting down and holding legs flexion and extension
description: Starting posture: Start with a high -level tablet support posture: back, arms, and legs are straight, and both hands are separated from the shoulders.  Step:  ol li Jump forward in the direction of the arms, keep the back straight./li li Hands with both hands, and the legs jump back to the high -level flat support position./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Forearm
description: Starting posture: Stand straight   Step:  ol li Straighten your arms, put it in front ofposture./li li As mentioned in step 1, repeat this set of action./li /ol

name: Frontal neck stretch
description: Starting position: sitting or standing, the back is straight.  Step:  ol li Open big mouth./li li Keep your mouth open and raise your head slowly.You can put your hands in your head to support your head./li li Slowly put on the mouth and then open./li li Finally, slowly return to the starting position and close the mouth./li /ol

name: Half -time Bobbing
description: 起始姿势：站直，双脚分开与臀部同宽。步骤：olli深蹲蹲下，双手放在膝盖之间脚前，支撑在地板上；背部挺直。/lili双手放在地板上，双腿向后跳到高平板支撑的位置。/lili双脚向前跳，回到下蹲位置。/lili跳起。/lili重复。/li/ol

name: Reverse bow
description: Starting posture: Standing straight, the feet are separated from the hips.  Step:  OL li A leg is stepped back to make the knee be curved comfortably into 90 degrees angle./li li Slowly bend your knees, with a 90 -degree angle of both knees./li li Back to the starting position./li li Change legs, repeat./li /ol

name: Right Baogalia Squat
description: ol li Standing straight in front of the chair, take a big step.Put the back of the other foot on the chair./li li Bend the front knee, keep a balance with the arm until the back knees almost touch the ground./li li back to the starting position and repeat./li /ol

name: Right front arm tablet support
description: 起始姿势：侧躺，下肘成直角，手臂伸出。 抬起下肩，将骨盆抬离地面，前臂停留在地面； 你的头、骨盆和脚应该在一条直线上。步骤：olli保持这个姿势。/li/ol

name: Squatting on the right leg side
description: Starting posture:  ol li Stand straight, cross the foot horizontally, making the distance between the feet slightly greater than the shoulder width./li /ol  Step:  ol li Bend a knee until your thigh is parallel to the ground.The curved knee must be a straight line with the feet./li li Push back to the starting posture./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: 右腿手枪式深蹲
description: ol li Stand with one leg, straighten the other leg, slightly move forward./li li Slowly bent the knee of one leg, squat, keep the back and the other leg straightened./li li Get up slowly from the squat state, straighten the bending knee, and keep the other leg straightened./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Right leg lifting
description: OL li Stand on the floor or on the edge of the steps to ensure that the range of movement is sufficient.Raise a leg and back on the lower leg./li li Lift the heels that support your feet and stand with your toes./li li Keep it for three seconds, and then drop the heel, but keep the heel without touching the ground./li /ol

name: Right leg and arrow squatting
description: Starting posture: Stand straight on the back.Take a big step forward.  Footsteps:  ol li Let the pelvis down until the right knee is almost touched./li li Raise the pelvis./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Right neck stretch
description: Starting posture: sitting or standing, the back is straight.  Step:  ol li Tour the head to one side./li li Grab the head from the other side with the closer hand./li li Hands with their heads, pushing their hands on their heads, to balance their strength, and keep their heads still./li li Keep this tension until the practice is over./li /ol

name: Rear neck stretch
description: Starting posture: Sit on a chair or a strong pillow.  Step:  ol li Exhale, tilt your head forward, chin against your chest, and put your hands behind your head./li li Gently pull the head with your hands, hold your head with your hands to balance with your hands./li li Persist for a while./li li Relax your arms and heads, open your shoulders slightly./li li Repeat this operation from step 2./li /ol

name: Four Union Bobby Jump
description: Starting posture: Standing straight, the feet are separated from the hips.  Step:  ol li Squat, put your hands on the feet between your knees, support it on the floor; the back is straight./li li Put your hands on the floor, and jump your legs back to the position of the high tablet support./li li Jump your feet forward and return to the squat position./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Basic skipping
description: Starting posture: both feet are closer, bend your knees slightly, keep your head and your body straight, keep your elbows inward, open your arms.  Step:  ol li Use enough power to turn the wrist only to turn the rope./li li jumping just makes the rope under the foot pass through the height./li li Repeat./li /ol  Note: This exercise requires a skipping rope.Make sure that the length of the rope is adjusted to the height that suits you.One check method is to grab two handles with one hand and stand in the middle of the rope hanging on the ground with one foot.If the rope (excluding the handle) just reaches the bottom of the chest, its length is appropriate.Short ropes will be dangerous because you may hurt yourself, and longer ropes will cause bad forms.

name: Big arm wound
description: Starting posture: Stand straight.  Step:  ol li Straighten your arms, turn to front of you, raise your head, put it behind, and finally return to the initial posture./li li As mentioned in step 1, repeat this set of action./li /ol

name: Infant
description: Starting posture: At the beginning, the limbs are on the ground, knees, toes, and hands touch the ground, and two big toes touch each other.  Step:  OL li Move your knees so that it is the same as the hip./li li exhale, while moving the pelvis backwards.Keep your hands touch the ground and sit on your foot./li li Relax the upper body, put the forehead on the ground, and move forward naturally./li li Keep this posture./li /ol  Tip:  ul li End this posture, you can retract your arms under your shoulder, move your upper body, and sit up./li /ul

name: Zuo Baogalia squatting leg squatting
description: ol li Standing straight in front of the chair, take a big step.Put the back of the other foot on the chair./li li Bend the front knee, keep a balance with the arm until the back knees almost touch the ground./li li back to the starting position and repeat./li /ol

name: Left front arm flat support
description: Starting posture: Lie on the side, the lower elbows into right angles, and the arm extend.Lift your lower shoulders, lift your pelvis away from the ground, and stay on the ground with your forearm; your head, pelvis and feet should be on a straight line.  Step:  om li Keep this posture./li /ol

name: Squatting on the left leg
description: Starting posture:  ol li Stand straight, cross the foot horizontally, making the distance between the feet slightly greater than the shoulder width./li /ol  Step:  ol li Bend a knee until your thigh is parallel to the ground.The curved knee must be a straight line with the feet./li li Push back to the starting posture./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Left -leg pistol squatting
description: ol li Stand with one leg, straighten the other leg, slightly move forward./li li Slowly bent the knee of one leg, squat, keep the back and the other leg straightened./li li Get up slowly from the squat state, straighten the bending knee, and keep the other leg straightened./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Left -leg lifting
description: olli站在地板上或者台阶的边缘上，保证运动范围足够。抬起一条腿，脚背靠在小腿上。/lili抬起支撑脚的脚跟，用脚尖站立。/lili保持三秒钟，然后落下脚跟，但保持脚跟不接触地面。/li/ol

name: Left -legged squatting
description: Starting posture: Stand straight on the back.Take a big step forward.  Footsteps:  ol li Let the pelvis down until the right knee is almost touched./li li Raise the pelvis./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Left neck stretch
description: Starting posture: sitting or standing, the back is straight.  Step:  ol li Tour the head to one side./li li Grab the head from the other side with the closer hand./li li Hands with their heads, pushing their hands on their heads, to balance their strength, and keep their heads still./li li Keep this tension until the practice is over./li /ol

name: Flat support
description: Starting posture:  OL li Limb to the ground.The arm is curved into a right corner, and the shoulder should be above the elbow.The back is straight, and the whole body is on a straight line./li /ol  Step:  ol li Keep this posture./li /ol

name: Bow
description: Starting posture: Stand straight on the back.  Step:  ol li A big step forward./li li Let the pelvis go down until your right knee almost touch the ground./li li Raise the pelvis./li li Return to the starting posture./li li Repeat, change your legs every time./li /ol

name: Tag up
description: Starting posture: First hang it on the horizontal bar, the palm of the hand, and the feet off the ground.Both hands are slightly wider than the shoulders.Don't be too wide, don't be on both sides of your body, in front of your body.The body should be straight and slightly forward.The arms should be stretched.  Step:  ol li Pull up your body evenly, so that your chest is close to the horizontal bar, and the chin is just over the horizontal pole.Don't jump or shake your body, such as kicking./li li Carefully put your body down and return to the starting position./li li Repeat it./li /ol  Reminder: —— To do it correctly, you must first enhance the power of several key parts, including shoulders, arms and abdominal muscles.You should accumulate sufficient strength through other exercises, and then start the traction upward.

name: Folding knife push -up
description: Starting posture: Below Dog: The body becomes a V -shaped, the back, arm and legs are straight, and the hips are raised in the air.You can first do a high -level flat support posture, and then move your hands backwards to form this posture.  Step:  ol li Bend the two elbows towards one side, keep the back and leg straight, and close the head close to the ground./li li Straighten your arms, push your hips back, and keep your back and leg straight./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Raising
description: Starting posture: lying on your back, your feet together, your arms on both sides of the body.  Step:  OL li Bend your knees, and then straighten it up to make your legs stand upright./li li Keep your legs straight and put down together without touching the ground.The lower the legs, the greater the strength of the exercise./li li The two legs are lifted together, and their legs stand upright again./li li Repeat from the second step./li /ol

name: Kettlebell
description: Starting location: standing position, the feet are the same as the hips, and the pot bell is located between the ankle.The back is straight and heads forward.  Step:  OL li Keep your back straight, use your hips as axis, bend your knees slightly, and put your hands on the handle of the pot./li li Grasp the pot bell and push your hands in the opposite direction, as if in a spring./li li When contacting the abdominal muscles and gluteal muscles, stand straight./li li Taking the hips again as the axis, put the pot bell back in situ, similar to step 1./li li Repeat from step 3./li /ol  Tip:  ul li Must do these actions in the correct way, otherwise it may cause injuries.For example, do not squat and do not use your hips as axis. Do not bend over when you reach out to get the kettlebell. Do not tilt backwards when you stand./li /ul

name: Chin
description: Starting posture: sitting or standing, the back is straight.  Step:  ol li Put your fingers on your chin and slowly put away your chin; the head moves backwards and align with the spine./li li Keep 5 seconds./li li The head returns to the normal position and repeats./li /ol

name: Bobby jump
description: Starting posture: Standing straight, the feet are separated from the hips.  Step:  ol li Squat, put your hands on the feet between your knees, support it on the floor; the back is straight./li li Put your hands on the floor, and jump your legs back to the position of the high tablet support./li li Do a push -up./li li Jump your feet forward and return to the squat position./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Squat
description: Starting posture: Standing, the feet are separated from the shoulders.  Step:  OL li Move your hips backwards and bend your knees and hips to reduce your torso until your hips are lower than the knee./li li Back to the initial posture./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Mountaineer
description: Starting posture: Start with an upright push -up posture, that is, the "high wooden board" posture.Both hands should be directly below the shoulder.Keep your head and back on a plane; facing the floor.The feet are separated by about the same width as the hips.  Step:  OL li Move one knee to the center of the body, move to the elbow, and keep the legs stretching./li li Get up quickly, straighten the curved legs, pull the other knee to the body./li li Repeat Step 2, alternate legs./li /ol  Note: During the whole process, keep the back as straight as possible to avoid humpback and back drooping.

name: Right -angle sitting wall
description: Starting posture: The back should be exposed to the wall, the knee becomes right and located directly above the angle.Faced to the front, the feet are separated from the shoulders, and stepping on the ground firmly.To reach this posture, you can lean on the wall and get about 2 feet from the wall.Slide down the wall and keep your back close to the wall until your knees become right corners.  Step:  om li Keep this posture./li /ol  Note: The tetrausal muscle pain is normal. If you feel the knee or knee bone pain, stop.

name: Summon squatting
description: Starting posture: Stand up, open your legs open, your toes out.  Step:  OL li Bend your knees outward, slowly sink down.Stretch your arms forward.The head, chest, and hip remain on a straight line.Squeeze the hips./li li Back to the starting position up./li li Repeat the above actions./li /ol

name: Shrugging
description: Starting position: sitting or standing, the back is straight.  Step:  ol li Lift your shoulders as much as possible and keep it for 5 seconds./li li Back to a relaxed position./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Shoulder heading forward
description: Starting posture: sitting or standing, the back is straight.  Step:  ol li Put your hands on your shoulders./li li Constantly rotate the shoulder joints on both sides at a moderate speed./li /ol

name: Shoulder around the shoulder
description: Starting posture: sitting or standing, the back is straight.  Step:  ol li Put your hands on your shoulders./li li Constantly rotate the shoulder joints on both sides at a moderate speed./li /ol

name: Kneeling and bend your knees and lift your legs
description: Starting posture: limbs to the ground.  Step:  ol li Push one foot backwards until it is completely stretched and focuses on the gluteal muscles.2. Stay for a second, and then return to the initial posture./li li Repeat, alternate your feet./li /ol

name: Hopping bamboo
description: Starting posture: Standing together on both feet, straight back, and arms on both sides.  Step:  ol li Open your legs, jump to a certain position with your hands./li li Jump back to the starting position./li li Repeat./li /ol

name: Turn around
description: Starting posture: sitting or standing, the back is straight, and the shoulders are down.  Step:  ol li Sit straight (stand straight) to relax the shoulders./li li Turn your head to one side as much as possible, stop when you feel obstructive and keep for 5 seconds./li li Back to the middle position, change edge, repeat./li /ol

name: High -level flat support
description: Starting posture: Start high flat flat support: hands and toes are in contact with the ground, the back is straight, and the arms and legs are straight.In this posture, you can lie on the ground, put your palms down on both sides of your head, and then lift and straighten your arms.  Step:  OL li Keep the beginning of the first posture throughout the exercise./li /ol

name: High -lifting
description: Starting posture: Stand straight.  Step:  OL li Run in place, raise your knees as much as possible to comfortable height, and quickly change your legs./li /ol
